name: 1975 Will Be The Death Of Me T-shirt
description:
In honor of Five Years of Artistic Adventuring, I'm bringing back one of my favorite personal graphics (from 2002!) and giving it a little twist using an early 1975 type treatment. It's been an amazing ride the last five years, and I can't wait for the next five!


Shirts are available for pick up at the gallery or will ship for a $5 flat fee (US) or $8 (everywhere else) shortly after the 5th.


Printed on a super soft Next Level 3600 (men's) and 3300 (women's) style shirt that fits true to size. White on Black, available in Men's and Women's sizes.

For local (Rochester) pickup, please select "Christmas Island" as your destination and we'll contact you to make arrangements for pickup at the gallery

name: VC - Crusher Destroyer - Steven Vogel
description: 12" x 12" one color silkscreen on coffee-stained paper. Signed with a rubber stamp, numbered edition of 75 Created by Steven Vogel from Black Lodges in conjunction with 1975 for 1975's five year anniversary show VOLO CALVARIAM. Each one is uniguely hand-coffee-stained. You can read a bit about the print and the show here: http://www.blacklodges.com/volo-calvariam-1975s-5-year-anniversary/ http://www.thereferencecouncil.com/2013/10/volo-calvariam/ We have designated three degrees of staining, please select which type you prefer and we will do our best to accommodate your request. (The pictured image would be considered "Cream and Sugar") Black - Heavy Staining Cream and Sugar - Somewhere in the middle Decaf - very even staining with fewer splotches The print will ship flat, hence the slightly higher shipping fee. Pickup at the gallery is available, please select "Christmas Island" as your shipping location. *For European customers, Steven will be soon offering these prints through BLACK LODGES to help save on shipping. From VOLO CALVARIAM. October 5 - November 2, 2013 All prices include 8% NYS sales tax.

name: 1975 x EvenOdd x Sweet Meat Co - Sarah C. Rutherford Holcomb Tote
description: For our 2012 Gallery rebuild fundraiser, we paired members of the Sweet Meat Co. with EvenOdd Creative to create one of a kind bags. The pictured tote features artwork by St. Monci. You will receive this exact bag when purchasing this item. All proceeds from the sale of these bags go to the costs of renovation of our new 1975 gallery space. Bear in mind there will be some natural chipping and wear through use due to the interaction of the paint and the sailcloth fabric, but this helps create a truly unique piece. Dimensions: 11" Wide x 14" Tall x 6" Deep Descriptions from the EvenOdd site: The Holcomb is a perfect carryall bag for your everyday travels. This bag is one of a kind - handmade in the USA from upcylced sailcloth + bike inner tubes. Tear and water resistant.    Important Note: Bags will vary slightly because each is made from different bike inner tubes and sailcloth. No two will be alike. Each inner tube is hand cut and then washed thoroughly with an eco-friendly detergent. The inner tube strips are then sewn together to make the "fabric quilt" for these products. Inner tubes may have worn or faded white brand markings and dimensional text on certain areas. For Rochester Pickup at the gallery, please select "Christmas Island" For more about our 2012 fundraiser: http://www.indiegogo.com/1975Gallery/x/290103

name: Chasing Marvelous Times - St. Monci
description:
8 colors screen print with graphite
12 x 12" 

This print marks the beginning of a partnership between 1975 and HTB Press to bring you high quality art prints at affordable prices. I began my own art collection by purchasing screenprints from artists I admired, eventually working my way into buying their original works. Releasing prints by the artists we support has always been a desire of mine, and I’m very excited to collaborate with HTB Press to finally make this happen.

The artwork was created specifically for the grand opening. All eight colors of each print were hand-pulled at HTB press and features special graphite hand embellishing and finishing by St. Monci, making every print unique. They are printed on 4-ply rag matboard with hand-rounded corners, the same surface/material that St. Monci uses for his original works. These are produced in a limited edition of 75 prints.

Printed by HTB Press - www.htbpress.com

Print ships flat.

Pickup at the gallery is available, please select "Christmas Island."

Price includes 8% NYS sales tax.
